			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><a href="http://necro.eqclasses.com/forum/topic.asp?TOPIC_ID=21625" target="_blank">http://necro.eqclasses.com/forum/topic.asp?TOPIC_ID=21625</a>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Regarding Item Upgrades: are these item upgrades for existing stats only? Or, are we able to add stats...ie....if the item has no STR on it originally, are we able to add STR? Or can we only increase the value of pre-existing stats.
<br />

<br />
Can we add focusses and/or procs/effects?
<br />

<br />
And this is sort of tied to LDoN.....once LDoN is released, will you start working on Critical DoTs for dot casters? Or are you already working on Crit Dots ?</span>
<br />

<br />
Yes, and augmentation can add new stats to an item. An item with no bonus to Int, for example, could be given a + Int with an augmentation.
<br />

<br />
Augmentations can add just about any effect that can be on an item (including procs). What effects will actually be attached to augmentations I can't tell you. :)  
<br />

<br />
Using "LDoN" in your questions doesn't really make the question relate to the expansion... but I talked to the spell guys and there are two parts to the answer. First, it doesn't really make a lot of sense for DoTs to "crit". They don't blow holes in people, hitting a critical spot doesn't really work. But it probably does make sense to add some sort of AA that would do something similar.
<br />

<br />
However, nothing like that is on the schedule of things to do real soon. Sorry.
<br />

<br />
A
<br />
 
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">With the huge disparity in players equipment...how will the dungeons be able to account for that in making it a challenging encounter?</span>
<br />

<br />
Players will have an option to choose a "hard" setting. If they want to take their uber gear and have an easier time with a "normal" setting for their level, that's their option. But choosing the hard option will yield a greater challenge and better rewards.
<br />

<br />
A
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">So by any effects you mean it's possible to add focus effects to items? Such as burning affliction 4 or affliction haste 4 for example or other focus effects that are only on a few items at the moment? </span>
<br />

<br />
I'm not 100% sure about focus effects, but I'm pretty sure that any effect that can go on an item can go on an augmentation.
<br />

<br />
Whether or not their will be any such items I can't tell you at this time. :)  
<br />

<br />
A
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">I got a question, how are the new spell lines coming out with LDoN, as to the necro line, maybe also the shaman line, they better?</span>
<br />

<br />
Spells are looking good. We've got some interesting new spell concepts for the expansion that I think you'll really like.
<br />

<br />
A
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Can you expand more on what these spells are, such as the spell reflection ones and pet ones?
<br />

<br />
Also, what do you see the place of the new line of curse dots to be? Their high mana cost, nonstandard specialization, low resist adjustment and high recast time make them pretty much unnecessary with our current line of DD spells for even a fast killing group setting</span>.
<br />

<br />
All I can tell you about the new dots is that we're tuning them to make them what we want, and something you folks will use.
<br />

<br />
I can probably touch on the reflection ones, they give a chance to turn the spell back on the caster. So if you are hit with a spell and it reflects, the caster will be affected. It's an awesome idea.
<br />

<br />
A
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">LDON seems to be a GROUP Dungeon based adventure. Will/IS there a adventure/quest for the solo?</span>
<br />

<br />
Keep in mind that these are instanced dungeons. Each time a group gets an adventure a new zone is created. We can only host so many zones. Also, individual content is very different than group content, so we can't just let a soloer hop into a group dungeon.
<br />

<br />
So the answer is, no, at this time we don't have any solo content. It's certainly possible, but right now due to hardware and time concerns, added to the factor that this is a multi-player game, we don't have any solo dungeons.
<br />

<br />
A
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">After adding and an Augment can it be removed for a different item? Example a +2 int +20 hp augment in a necklace can be taken out and then be put into a wrist slot item. Almost like removing them from one bag and putting it into another.</span>
<br />

<br />
You can remove an augment, but you have to disolve it to do so. The original item will not be harmed.
<br />

<br />
A
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Am I correct in that there will be no new Alternate Advancement in LDoN? Will the rewards be adequate enough on the 'hard' setting to give someone in the highest end gear with their alternate advancement maxed out any incentive to buy this expansion?</span>
<br />

<br />
Correct, no new AAs.
<br />

<br />
Well, we think so. Success in adventures awards points. With those points you can purchase items from the Wayfarers. Completing a harder adventure gets you more points (and better loot in the dungeon). Since you're picking what you get as a reward, you should be able to find something you like.
<br />

<br />
A
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">My questions,when LDoN comes out will it have dungeons we would be "Needed" in or will it be another "Trinity" exspansion?
<br />
Frankly from what i have heard "Rumors and occasional releases" it sounds like a nice set up but mostly for the "Trinity" 
<br />

<br />
If a group goes in with 5 members "Uber" equipted ,Elemental planes, Gods items etc,and thier 6th member is "Average" store bought gear will LDoN takes this into account or will it be as if all members were geared the same since the majority of them are "Uber" ?
<br />

<br />
Lastly will there be provisions in the "Future" for soloers and/or partners for LDoN? </span>
<br />

<br />

<br />
Well, I don't think that the "trinity" is that big of a deal. I'm pretty sure that a discussion about that won't net us anything... :)  
<br />

<br />
It's up to the group to decide how hard they want the challenge to be.
<br />

<br />
There's a posibility that we could add solo or duo adventures, but I don't know of any plans for it.
<br />

<br />
A
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">What is the one thing that YOU think is most likely to make the Necros of Norrath stand back and say "whoah, that's awesome!"?</span>
<br />

<br />
Interesting question...
<br />

<br />
There are two, and one I don't think I can mention yet, sorry. The other is some of the new spell effects. Simply awesome.
<br />

<br />
But then, I'm more of a roleplayer than a power gamer, so I may not be impressed by the stats on a new item or a new spell. :)  
<br />

<br />
A
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">How will These dungeon instances fit in on the red servers? Will they be safe havens or will agressive player killers be able to interupt the instance?
<br />

<br />
And will these augmentations stack. Meaning I can give one item str and int or is it limited to just one augmentation?</span>
<br />
 
<br />
Once you accept and adventure, it's yours. Only your group can get in. Though I do see that there might be issues at the entry points and at the Wayfarer camps. I'll pass that to the team...
<br />

<br />
I'm not sure about stacking. I do know that you shouldn't be able to put the same augment on the same item twice. If I had to guess, I'd say that only the best bonus on the same stat will work, but that's just a guess. But some items can have more than one augmentation, and you could add a + int and a + str augmentation to such an item.
<br />

<br />
A
<br />
 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Will the placement of the mobs also be random so that you can never count on the same mobs being at the same spot</span>
<br />

<br />
Yes and no. Every set of content (and there are thousands) was hand created. So they are bound to vary some. But there are only so many places you can put an orc, you know? :)   So there will certainly be a limit to the variations. But keep in mind that there are 48 dungeons.
<br />

<br />
A
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">I keep hearing the refrence to the LIMITS on the number of instances ie simultanios adventure zones being in motion. Will there be a waiting list if there is to much in motion or are we to expect a bunch of people smamming a guy to see who gets Flaged to do the next avaible adventure???</span>
<br />

<br />
Any limits will be purely hardware. We can only host so many instances before we run out of memory or Scott Hartsman's head lights on fire. We can, however, host a LOT of instances. It doesn't look like we'll have a problem, but it will be one of the most important things for us to watch on launch day.
<br />

<br />
A
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Will zone-ins be "Safe" or will they have a few dungeons with mobs guarding them?</span>
<br />

<br />
The zone in portals are not in extremely dangerous places.
<br />

<br />
A
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">will named mobs be up for every group, but not always the same guy, or will it be that sometimes a group wont get a named up like a real old fashioned hunt?</span>
<br />

<br />
Depends on your task. If you were sent to kill someone, he'll be there. If you're on a rescue mission, the damsel will indeed be in distress.
<br />

<br />
A
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">How will you be able to tell which dungeon is easiest or hardest? Will the quest giver ask you your preferrence?</span>
<br />

<br />
It doesn't work quite like that. What you'll be able to do is tell the Wayfarer that you think you can handle a tough job, and he'll send you on a tough adventure. Which dungeon he sends you into won't be as important.
<br />

<br />
A</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
